Tick survival depends on several factors, including climate
suitability, host density, soil composition, and microhabitat char-
acteristics (Leighton et al. 2012). Ogden et al. (2005, 2006, 2008)
raised the hypothesis that climate suitability, predominantly tem-
perature, is a key determinant of the survival of
populations and consequently that a warming climate may be a
key driver of the emergence of the tick in Canada. There are mul-
